'''ABC South Coast''' is an [[ABC Local Radio]] station based in [[Albany, Western Australia|Albany]]. The station broadcasts to the coastal parts of the [[Great Southern (Western Australia)|Great Southern]] region of [[Western Australia]]. This includes the towns of [[Denmark, Western Australia|Denmark]] and [[Mount Barker, Western Australia|Mount Barker]].
The station began broadcasting as '''6AL''' in 1956. There are a number of low power FM transmitters as well. Local programs are also broadcast through [[ABC Great Southern]].
When local programs are not broadcast the station is a relay of [[720 ABC Perth]].
